{"title_page": "List of watermills in the United Kingdom", "text_new": "{{short description|Wikipedia list article}}\nThe use of water power in Britain was at its peak just before the [[Industrial Revolution]]. The need for power was great and [[steam power]] had not yet become established. It is estimated that at this time there were well in excess of ten thousand [[watermill]]s in the country.  Most of these were [[wheat|corn]] mills (to grind [[flour]]), but almost any industrial process needing motive power, beyond that available from the muscles of men or animals, used a [[water wheel]], unless a [[windmill]] was preferred.\n\nToday only a fraction of these mills survive. Many are used as private residences, or have been converted into offices or flats. A small number have been preserved or restored as museums where the public can see the mill in operation.\n[[Image:Kingsbury Water Mill 20031012-007.jpg|thumb|Kingsbury Watermill Museum, St Albans]]\n\nThis is a list of some of the surviving and demolished '''[[watermill]]s and [[tide mill]]s in the [[United Kingdom]]'''.\n{{quote box\n| title = The Lesson of the Water Mill\n| quote =&nbsp;<br>\nListen to the water mill<br>\nThrough the livelong day;<br>\nHow the clicking of the wheel<br>\nWears the hours away.<br>\nLanguidly the autumn wind<br>\nStirs the withered leaves;<br>\nOn the field the reapers sing<br>\nBinding up the sheaves;<br>\nAnd a proverb haunts my mind<br>\nAnd as a spell is cast,<br>\n\"The mill will never grind<br>\nWith the water that has passed.\"<br>\n&nbsp;\n| source = [[Sarah Doudney]],\n| align = right\n| width = 210px\n| fontsize = \n| bgcolor = aliceblue\n| style =\n| title_bg =\n| title_fnt =\n| tstyle = text-align: centre;\n| qalign = right\n| qstyle = text-align: left;\n| quoted = yes\n| salign = right\n| sstyle = text-align: right;}}\n\n== England ==\n\n===Bedfordshire===\n[[File:Stotfold Mill, Mill Lane - geograph.org.uk - 159395.jpg|thumb|Stotfold Mill, Bedfordshire]]\n*Bowman's Watermill, [[Astwick]]\n*Broham Watermill, [[Bromham, Bedfordshire|Broham]]\n*Clophill Watermill, [[Clophill]]\n*[[Stotfold Watermill]], Stotfold\n*The Olde Watermill, [[Barton-le-Clay]]\n{{-}}\n\n===Berkshire===\n[[File:Chamberhouse Mill.jpg|thumb|Chamberhouse Mill, Berkshire]]\n*[[Abbey Mill, Reading|Abbey Mill]], [[Reading, Berkshire|Reading]]\n*[[Calcot Mill]], Reading\n*[[Chamberhouse Mill]], [[Thatcham]]\n*[[Hungerford Mill]], Thatcham\n*[[Watermill Theatre]], [[Bagnor]]\n\n===Buckinghamshire===\n[[File:Hambleden Mill and Weir - geograph.org.uk - 536842.jpg|thumb|Hambleden Mill, Buckinghamshire]]\n*[[Ford End Mill]], [[Ivinghoe]]\n*[[Hambleden Mill]], [[Hambleden]]\n*[[Pann Mill]], [[High Wycombe]]\n{{-}}\n\n===Cambridgeshire===\n[[File:Cmglee Houghton Mill.jpg|thumb|Houghton Mill, Cambridgeshire]]\n*[[Hinxton Mill]], [[Hinxton]]\n*[[Houghton Mill]], Houghton\n*[[Lode Watermill]], [[Lode, Cambridgeshire|Lode]]\n*[[Thornhaugh|Sacrewell Mill]], [[Peterborough]]\n*[[Soham Mill]], [[Soham]]\n\n===Cheshire===\n[[File:Quarry Bank Mill 2016 027.jpg|thumb|Quarry Bank Mill, Cheshire]]\n*[[Bunbury Mill]], Bunbury\n*[[Dee Mills - site of]], [[Chester]]\n*[[Dunham Massey Sawmill]], [[Altrincham]]\n*[[Nantwich#Nantwich Mill|Nantwich Mill]], [[Nantwich]]\n*[[Nether Alderley Mill]], Macclesfield\n*[[Quarry Bank Mill]], Styal\n*[[Stretton Watermill]], Stretton\n*[[Trafford Mill]], Mickle Trafford, Chester\n*[[Walk Mill]], Waverton, Cheshire<ref>[http://www.walkmillflour.co.uk/ Walk Mill Official Website]</ref> Built 2008\n\n===Cornwall===\n[[File:The watermill at Cotehele - geograph.org.uk - 1616255.jpg|thumb|Cotehele Mill, Cornwall]]\n*Bar Pool Mill, [[Falmouth, Cornwall|Falmouth]]\n*Carbeal Tide Mill, [[Torpoint]]\n*Cotehele Mill, [[Calstock]]\n*Dinham Tide Mill, [[St Minver]]\n*Gerrans Sea Mill, [[Gerrans]]\n*Hingham Mill, near [[Wadebridge]]\n*Kestle Mill, [[Kestle]]\n*Little Petherick Creek tide mill, [[Little Petherick]]\n*Penpoll tidemill, [[Feock, Cornwall|Feock]]\n*P