{"title_page": "Salisu Buhari", "text_new": "{{multiple issues|{{Copy edit|date=March 2020}}\n{{POV|date=September 2014}}}}\n\n'''Salisu Buhari''' is a former Speaker of The House of the [[House of Representatives (Nigeria)|House of Representatives of Nigeria]]. In 1999, he resigned from office over the allegations of certificate forgery. He was later convicted of certificate forgery and sentenced to two years in prison with an option of fine. He paid the fine and was later pardoned by President [[Olusegun Obasanjo]].\n\n==Political Career==\nBuhari had been a businessman before his political career. In 1999, Buhari was the speaker of the [[House of Representatives (Nigeria)|Nigeria House of Representatives]], which placed him in the 4th highest office in Nigeria. However, this only lasted for six weeks before his [[University of Toronto]] scandal and the beginning of what was known as the University of Toronto Saga. The scandal ultimately led to his resignation and prosecution.\n\n==Controversies==\nThe news of his age and certificate forgery first broke out on 16 February 1999 by an investigative news publication, [[TheNews magazine]]. Their investigation concluded that Buhari was born in 1970 and not 1963 as he claimed, and also that he did not graduate from the University of Toronto. The article published about the speaker dispelled that the speaker did not attended the university, not to talk of graduating. Section 65(1) of the 1999 Constitution of the Federal Republic of Nigeria disqualifies anyone below the age of 30 from running for membership of the House of Representatives.\n\nBuhari had also claimed that he completed his '''[[National Youth Service Corps|National Youth Service]]''' at Standard Construction in [[Kano]] which was also not true, as his name could not be found in any record in the list of those who completed the scheme. When Buhari was confronted with multiple allegations about his declaration and falsification, he promptly responded accusing the publications as an attack on him and proclaims his innocence and threatened to file a lawsuit against the publisher for libel. His confidence and response to the allegations were very assertive in nature and quite convincing that he was a victim of a witch-hunt. The magazine had written to the University of Toronto, requesting confirmation that Buhari was an alumnus. In response, Carlo Villanueva, an official of the Institution wrote, \u201c''Regarding your request for confirmation of degree for Mr Ibrahim Salisu Buhari. We have searched our records and could not find anybody with the name you are inquiring with.''\u201d\n\nHe had been found guilty in the court of public opinion and among in the halls where policies are made and sentences are meted out, the tension had reached a fever pitch.\n\nIn 23 July 1999, disgraced and cornered, Buhari faced [[Nigerians]] and admitted to falsifying his age and forging certificates as well as other contents of the News report.\n\n\u201c''I apologize to you. I apologize to the nation. I apologize to my family and friends for all the distress I have caused them. I was misled in error by a zeal to serve the nation, I hope the nation will forgive me and give me the opportunity to serve again.''\u201d\n\nHe resigned from his membership of the House of Representatives in 1999.\n\nIn 2013, he was chosen as part of the governing council of the [[University of Nigeria]] by the [[Federal government of Nigeria|Nigerian government]].<ref name=\"saharareporters\">{{cite news|url=http://saharareporters.com/2013/07/05/salisu-buhari-member-unn-governing-council-no-please|title=Salisu Buhari, A Member of UNN Governing Council? No Please!|last=Igbokwe|first=Joe|date=5 July 2013|work=[[Sahara Reporters]]|accessdate=5 September 2014}}</ref><ref name=\"nigeriapoliticsonline\">{{cite web|url=http://nigeriapoliticsonline.com/tinubu-guilty-of-certificate-forgery-like-salisu-buhari-obasanjo/|title=Tinubu guilty of certificate forgery like Salisu Buhari  &#8211;Obasanjo|date=14 August 2013|website=Nigeria Politics Online|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140905053505/http://nigeriapoliticsonline.com/tinubu-guilty-of-certificate-forgery-like-salisu-buhari-obasanjo/|archivedate=5 September 2014|url-status=dead|accessdate=5 September 2014}}</ref><ref name=\"9jabook\">{{cite web|url=http://www.9jabook.com/forum/topics/disgraced-fmr-speaker-salisu-buhari-of-toronto-university-forged-|title=Disgraced Fmr Speaker Salisu Buhari of &quot;Toronto University forged certificate&quot;  Now in UNN Governing council|date=4 April 2013|website=9jabook|accessdate=5 September 2014}}</ref>{{Unreliable source?|date=July 2018}}<ref>{{cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/africa/401123.stm|title=World: Africa {{!}} Nigerian speaker quits in tears|date=22 July 1999|work=[[BBC News]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thescoopng.com/abati-defends-appointment-of-certificate-forger-salisu-buhari-as-unn-governing-council-member/|title=Abati defends appointment of certificate forger, Salisu Buhari, as UNN governing council member|last=Lawal|first=Dare|date=14 April 2013|website=The ScoopNG}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}https://www.pulse.ng/gist/pop-culture/the-story-of-salisu-buhari-and-the-toronto-university-saga-id8022958.html\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Buhari, Salisu}}\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:University of Nigeria, Nsukka people]]\n", "text_old": "{{multiple issues|{{Copy edit|date=March 2020}}\n{{POV|date=September 2014}}}}\n\n'''Salisu Buhari''' is a former Speaker of The House of the [[House of Representatives (Nigeria)|House of Representatives of Nigeria]]. In 1999, he resigned from office over the allegations of certificate forgery. He was later convicted of certificate forgery and sentenced to two years in prison with an option of fine. He paid the fine and was later pardoned by President [[Olusegun Obasanjo]].\n\n==Political Career==\nBuhari had been a businessman before his political career. In 1999, Buhari was the speaker of the [[House of Representatives (Nigeria)|Nigeria House of Representatives]], which placed him in the 4th highest office in Nigeria. However, this only lasted for six weeks before his [[University of Toronto]] scandal and the beginning of what was known as the University of Toronto Saga. The scandal ultimately led to his resignation and prosecution.\n\n==Controversies==\nThe news of his age and certificate forgery first broke out on 16 February 1999 by an investigative news publication, [[TheNews magazine]]. Their investigation concluded that Buhari was born in 1970 and not 1963 as he claimed, and also that he did not graduate from the University of Toronto. The article published about the speaker dispelled that the speaker did not attended the university, not to talk of graduating. Section 65(1) of the 1999 Constitution of the Federal Republic of Nigeria disqualifies anyone below the age of 30 from running for membership of the House of Representatives.\n\nBuhari had also claimed that he completed his '''[[National Youth Service Corps|National Youth Service]]''' at Standard Construction in [[Kano]] which was also not true, as his name could not be found on any record in the list of those who completed the scheme. When Buhari was confronted with multiple allegations about his declaration and falsification, he promptly responded accusing the publications as an attack on him and proclaims his innocence and threatened to file a lawsuit against the publisher for libel. His confidence and response to the allegations were very assertive in nature and quite convincing that he was a victim of a witch-hunt. The magazine had written to the University of Toronto, requesting confirmation that Buhari was an alumnus. In response, Carlo Villanueva, an official of the Institution wrote, \u201c''Regarding your request for confirmation of degree for Mr Ibrahim Salisu Buhari. We have searched our records and could not find anybody with the name you are inquiring with.''\u201d\n\nHe had been found guilty in the court of public opinion and among in the halls where policies are made and sentences are meted out, the tension had reached a fever pitch.\n\nIn 23 July 1999, disgraced and cornered, Buhari faced [[Nigerians]] and admitted to falsifying his age and forging certificates as well as other contents of the News report.\n\n\u201c''I apologize to you. I apologize to the nation. I apologize to my family and friends for all the distress I have caused them. I was misled in error by zeal to serve the nation, I hope the nation will forgive me and give me the opportunity to serve again.''\u201d\n\nHe resigned from his membership of the House of Representatives in 1999.\n\nIn 2013, he was chosen as part of the governing council of the [[University of Nigeria]] by the [[Federal government of Nigeria|Nigerian government]].<ref name=\"saharareporters\">{{cite news|url=http://saharareporters.com/2013/07/05/salisu-buhari-member-unn-governing-council-no-please|title=Salisu Buhari, A Member of UNN Governing Council? No Please!|last=Igbokwe|first=Joe|date=5 July 2013|work=[[Sahara Reporters]]|accessdate=5 September 2014}}</ref><ref name=\"nigeriapoliticsonline\">{{cite web|url=http://nigeriapoliticsonline.com/tinubu-guilty-of-certificate-forgery-like-salisu-buhari-obasanjo/|title=Tinubu guilty of certificate forgery like Salisu Buhari  &#8211;Obasanjo|date=14 August 2013|website=Nigeria Politics Online|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140905053505/http://nigeriapoliticsonline.com/tinubu-guilty-of-certificate-forgery-like-salisu-buhari-obasanjo/|archivedate=5 September 2014|url-status=dead|accessdate=5 September 2014}}</ref><ref name=\"9jabook\">{{cite web|url=http://www.9jabook.com/forum/topics/disgraced-fmr-speaker-salisu-buhari-of-toronto-university-forged-|title=Disgraced Fmr Speaker Salisu Buhari of &quot;Toronto University forged certificate&quot;  Now in UNN Governing council|date=4 April 2013|website=9jabook|accessdate=5 September 2014}}</ref>{{Unreliable source?|date=July 2018}}<ref>{{cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/africa/401123.stm|title=World: Africa {{!}} Nigerian speaker quits in tears|date=22 July 1999|work=[[BBC News]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thescoopng.com/abati-defends-appointment-of-certificate-forger-salisu-buhari-as-unn-governing-council-member/|title=Abati defends appointment of certificate forger, Salisu Buhari, as UNN governing council member|last=Lawal|first=Dare|date=14 April 2013|website=The ScoopNG}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}https://www.pulse.ng/gist/pop-culture/the-story-of-salisu-buhari-and-the-toronto-university-saga-id8022958.html\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Buhari, Salisu}}\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:University of Nigeria, Nsukka people]]\n", "name_user": "Chirag.Saluja", "label": "safe", "comment": "Grammar changes", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Salisu_Buhari"}
{"title_page": "Peacock (streaming service)", "text_new": "{{short description|American streaming video service}}\n{{Infobox website\n| name             = Peacock\n| logo             = NBCUniversal Peacock Logo.svg\n| collapsible      = \n| screenshot       = \n| screenshot_size  = \n| screenshot_alt   = \n| caption          = \n| type             = [[Over-the-top media services|OTT platform]]\n| foundation       = \n| location         = [[30 Rockefeller Plaza]], [[New York City]], [[New York (state)|New York]]\n| country          = U.S.\n| area served      = \n| founder          = \n| CEO              = \n| key_people       = Matt Strauss ([[Chairperson|Chairman]])\n| services         = \n| revenue          = \n| operating_income = \n| international    = \n| parent           = [[NBCUniversal Cable Entertainment Group#NBCUniversal Direct-to-Consumer and Digital Enterprises|NBCUniversal Direct-to-Consumer and Digital Enterprises]]\n| url              = {{Official url}}\n| launched         = {{ubl|{{Start date|2020|04|15}} ([[Xfinity]] customers)|{{start date and age|2020|07|15}}}}\n| alexa            = \n| advertising      = \n| registration     = \n| users            = \n| language         = \n| current_status   = Operating \n}}\n'''Peacock''' is an upcoming American [[Over-the-top media services|over-the-top]] [[subscription video on demand]] [[Streaming media|streaming]] service by [[NBCUniversal]], a subsidiary of [[Comcast]]. Named after the [[logo of NBC]], the service is set to launch on July 15, 2020, with early availability for [[Xfinity]] customers starting on April 15, 2020.<ref name=\"deadline\">{{cite web|last=Andreeva|first=Nellie|title=NBCU Streamer Gets Name, Sets Slate Of Reboots, 'Dr. Death', Ed Helms & Amber Ruffin Series, 'Parks & Rec'|url=https://deadline.com/2019/09/nbcu-streamer-peacock-name-slate-of-reboots-dr-death-mike-schur-ed-helms-series-amber-ruffin-parks-recreation-1202736689|work=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|date=September 17, 2019|accessdate=September 17, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190917185437/https://deadline.com/2019/09/nbcu-streamer-peacock-name-slate-of-reboots-dr-death-mike-schur-ed-helms-series-amber-ruffin-parks-recreation-1202736689/|archive-date=September 17, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"nytimes\">{{cite web|last=Sperling|first=Nicole|title=NBCUniversal Introduces Peacock, Its New Streaming Service|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2019/09/17/business/media/peacock-nbcuniversal-streaming.html|work=[[The New York Times]]|date=September 17, 2019|accessdate=September 17, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190917130802/https://www.nytimes.com/2019/09/17/business/media/peacock-nbcuniversal-streaming.html|archive-date=September 17, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"hollywoodreporter\">{{cite web|last=Goldberg|first=Lesley|title=NBCUniversal's Streaming Strategy, Name, Programming Lineup Revealed|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/nbcuniversals-streaming-strategy-name-programming-lineup-revealed-1240157|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|date=September 17, 2019|accessdate=September 17, 2019|language=en|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190917133143/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/nbcuniversals-streaming-strategy-name-programming-lineup-revealed-1240157|archive-date=September 17, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==History==\nOn January 14, 2019, [[NBCUniversal]] announced that it will launch an [[Over-the-top media services|over-the-top]] [[Streaming media|streaming service]] in 2020, featuring content from its entertainment brands. It was also announced that the service would be free and ad-supported for customers of NBCUniversal pay-TV, [[Comcast]], and eventually [[Sky (company)|Sky]]; viewers without a pay-TV subscription or viewers who do not want advertisements can also subscribe to an ad-free version of the service. NBCUniversal also announced at that time a reorganization created [[NBCUniversal Cable Entertainment Group#NBCUniversal Direct-to-Consumer and Digital Enterprises|NBCUniversal Direct-to-Consumer and Digital Enterprises]] under [[Chairperson|Chairman]] [[Bonnie Hammer]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=Hayes |first1=Dade |title=NBCUniversal Entering The Streaming Wars With 2020 Launch Of Bonnie Hammer-Run Service; Mark Lazarus, Jeff Shell Also Get Major Promotions |url=https://deadline.com/2019/01/nbcuniversal-entering-the-streaming-wars-with-2020-launch-of-bonnie-hammer-run-service-mark-lazarus-jeff-schell-get-major-promotions-1202534914 |website=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |accessdate=September 17, 2019 |date=January 14, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191030214327/https://deadline.com/2019/01/nbcuniversal-entering-the-streaming-wars-with-2020-launch-of-bonnie-hammer-run-service-mark-lazarus-jeff-schell-get-major-promotions-1202534914/ |archive-date=October 30, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nOn September 17, 2019, NBCUniversal announced that the service would be called Peacock and would be available in April 2020. The announcement also included new original programming, NBCU property reboots, and that [[NBC]] series ''[[The Office (American TV series)|The Office]]'' and ''[[Parks and Recreation]]'' would be taken off from rival streaming services [[Netflix]], [[Hulu]], and [[Prime Video]]. The series would join the service once their exclusive streaming rights to rival streaming services expire, with ''Parks and Recreation'' joining in October 2020 and ''The Office'' joining in January 2021.<ref name=\"deadline\" /><ref>{{cite web |last1=Andreeva |first1=Nellie |title='Parks & Recreation' To Join 'The Office' On Peacock NBCU Streaming Service |url=https://deadline.com/2019/09/parks-recreation-acquired-peacock-join-the-office-nbcu-streaming-service-1202736698 |website=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |accessdate=September 17, 2019 |date=September 17, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190918010048/https://deadline.com/2019/09/parks-recreation-acquired-peacock-join-the-office-nbcu-streaming-service-1202736698/ |archive-date=September 18, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nOn December 23, 2019, Comcast announced that NBCUniversal would bring content from [[Lionsgate]] to Peacock, as part of a long-term carriage deal with Lionsgate's subsidiary [[Starz]], eight days before the December 31 expiration date for the previous contract.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Hayes |first1=Dade |title=Comcast And Starz Reach Carriage Deal; Lionsgate, NBCUniversal Swap Streaming Fare \u2013 Update |url=https://deadline.com/2019/12/comcast-and-starz-reach-carriage-deal-with-lionsgate-nbcuniversal-content-pact-1202816318/ |website=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |accessdate=December 23, 2019 |date=December 23, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191223180308/https://deadline.com/2019/12/comcast-and-starz-reach-carriage-deal-with-lionsgate-nbcuniversal-content-pact-1202816318/ |archive-date=December 23, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nOn January 16, 2020, Comcast announced that Peacock would debut for [[Xfinity]] cable and broadband customers on April 15, 2020, and will be made available for everyone in the United States on July 15, 2020.<ref name=\"variety-peacock-pricing\">{{Cite web|url=https://variety.com/2020/tv/news/nbc-peacock-pricing-launch-date-1203469722/|title=NBCU's Peacock Pricing and Launch Date Announced|last=Spangler|first=Todd|date=2020-01-16|website=Variety|language=en|access-date=2020-01-16}}</ref>  Additionally, Comcast announced additional programming details, including [[NBC Sports]] content such as non-televised [[Premier League]] soccer matches and extended coverage of the [[Ryder Cup]] and [[2020 Summer Olympics]], duplicating content that is a part of [[NBC Sports Gold]] (though without some features of Gold such as on-demand replays for Premier League matches).<ref>{{cite news|url=https://worldsoccertalk.com/2020/01/16/nbcs-peacock-premium-streaming-service-to-include-premier-league-games/|title=NBC\u2019s Peacock premium streaming service to include Premier League games|last=Harris|first=Christopher|date=16 January 2019|publisher=World Soccer Talk|accessdate=17 January 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200117060502/https://worldsoccertalk.com/2020/01/16/nbcs-peacock-premium-streaming-service-to-include-premier-league-games/|archive-date=17 January 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nIn February 2020, [[A&E Networks]] licensed some titles from the [[A&E (TV channel)|A&E]] and [[History (American TV channel)|History]] libraries to Peacock.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Skilton |first1=Alison |title=Peacock & A+E Networks Pact for Content Deal |url=https://worldscreen.com/tvreal/peacock-ae-networks-pact-for-content-deal/ |accessdate=February 27, 2020 |work=TVREAL |date=February 27, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200227204426/https://worldscreen.com/tvreal/peacock-ae-networks-pact-for-content-deal/ |archive-date=February 27, 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n==Service structure==\nPeacock will have two programming tiers, both of which will be supported by [[advertising]] (limited to five minutes per hour) by default: Peacock Free, which will be available at no charge to all U.S. Internet users, but with a reduced programming lineup; and Peacock Premium, which will be included at no charge for subscribers to participating TV service providers including Xfinity and [[Cox Communications]], and $5 per month for others. Subscribers to Peacock Premium, whether included through their provider or paid separately, can upgrade to an ad-free version for an additional $5 per month.<ref name=\"variety-peacock-pricing\" />\n\n==Content==\n===Original programming===\n====Series====\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"width:100%;\"\n|-\n! Title\n! Genre\n! Premiere\n! Seasons\n! Length\n! Status\n! Production\n! scope=\"col\" class=\"unsortable\" |  Notes\n|-\n| {{sort|Amber Ruffin|''The [[Amber Ruffin]] Show''}}\n| {{ubl|Talk show}}\n| {{TableTBA}}\n| {{TableTBA}}\n| {{TableTBA}}